  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>The Hotel Bristol staff are known for their warm welcome and accommodating nature. Grab a drink and head to the sun terrace to appreciate the impressive peaks or experience the kitchens local dishes using ingredients from the region, including some wonderful cheeses, meats and wine options.</span></p>
<h2><span>Ski-in/ski-out</span></h2>
<p><span>If you're looking for a warm, friendly hotel with ski-in/ski-out facilities then the Hotel Bristol is the ideal choice. Located adjacent to the ski slopes and ski school meeting point, the hotel gives you easy access to the slopes while still being in the centre of town. </span><span></span></p>
<h2><span>Attractive rooms</span></h2>
<p><span>The rooms are bright and have recently been renovated along with the common areas in a traditional Swiss style. All standard rooms have south facing balconies which look out over the piste, making it the ideal spot to watch skiers and snowboarders as they come down off the mountain. </span></p>
<h2>Relaxation</h2>
<p>During your stay at Hotel Bristol, you can take a moment to relax and connect with your body. The new yoga, pilates, and meditation classes offered by the hotel are an amazing way to regenerate after a hard day on the slopes. </p>]]></description>
